ekko.actor.warn-about-java-serializer-usage = off, then terminate ActorSystems cleanly.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Pekko documentation lists pekko-testkit as a test-scoped helper for classic actor testing, but it is optional for meaningful reachability coverage because actor systems, Props, ask/pattern APIs, serialization, config, DNS, and dispatch classes are available from pekko-actor itself.\",\n    \"Keeping the existing 1.1.5 TypedActor tests will continue to fail compilation on 2.0.0-M1.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d60a974f43c7c7c016a42bf7454a48193a2d5bb82ea37ac3b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2077, "output": 1270, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30483, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782759268041, "responseId": "resp_0d60a974f43c7c7c016a42bf64ae78819386fc8fc0917f875e"}}
